.alert.alert-light.border
  %h3.fw-semibold.mb-2 Goal of this page
  %p.mb-3
    Scan company-visible goals and their linked contributors so you can judge how confident to be
    in higher-level goals—without using a spreadsheet as the source of truth.

  %h3.fw-semibold.mb-2 Context
  %p.mb-3
    Goals can link as parents and children (GoalLinks). Confidence checks on child goals are a signal
    for how the work under a company or team goal is going. A goal's
    %strong Commit / Stretch / Transform
    label is its
    %em initial
    confidence designation—set when the goal starts—not a live status color.

  %h3.fw-semibold.mb-2 Specifics of this page
  %h5.fw-semibold.mb-2 What you see
  %ul.mb-3
    %li
      Only goals with visibility
      %strong everyone in company
    %li Expand/collapse the full linked descendant tree
    %li
      Next to each title, a subtle pill shows
      %strong initial confidence – goal type
      (hover for Commit / Stretch / Transform meaning)
    %li Each row shows that goal's latest confidence check
    %li
      Parents with children show an
      %strong advisory
      distribution of descendant
      %em latest
      confidence (≥80% / 50–79% / &lt;50% / no check-in), plus an optional average

  %h5.fw-semibold.mb-2 How to read the rollup
  %ul.mb-0
    %li Rollup chips summarize latest check-ins on linked descendants—not Commit/Stretch/Transform designations
    %li The average is secondary context only—it does not set the parent's confidence check
    %li
      Create and edit goals on the main
      = link_to "Goals", organization_goals_path(@organization, owner_id: "everyone_in_company")
      page
